                </p>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">The Triple-Screen ‘Horizon View’ Experience</span></p>

                <p>The central talking point of the Sierra's high-end trims is the segment-first <span class="font-weight-700">Horizon View Triple Screen Infotainment Experience. </span>This setup places three displays—the digital driver cluster, the main infotainment touchscreen, and a dedicated <span class="font-weight-700">Passenger Screen</span>—under a seamless sheet of glass.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Driver & Co-Driver Focus:</span> The digital screens provide a highly customizable interface, integrating the <span class="font-weight-700">Arcade Suite</span> with over 28 apps for entertainment and utility. This allows the front passenger to enjoy media or navigation without distracting the driver.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Digital Command Center: </span>The driver interacts with a sleek<span class="font-weight-700"> Digital Steering with Illuminated Logo.</span> Enhancing the driving experience is the revolutionary<span class="font-weight-700"> HypAR HUD (Head-Up Display) </span>with Multicolour Guides, a technology debut for an Indian homegrown ICE vehicle, projecting vital information directly onto the windshield.</li>
